Build succeeds (the warning is pre-existing, unrelated to the migration). Here's what changed:

**`[ExpectedException]` → `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()`**

```csharp
// Before (MSTest v3)
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void MyTest()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After (MSTest v4)
[TestMethod]
public void MyTest()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

**Why it's better:** the assertion pinpoints exactly which line should throw, rather than treating the entire method body as the "expected throw zone." It also returns the caught exception so you can further inspect its message or properties if needed.
